    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about needing an escrow account for this house i'm looking at in toronto. what actually is escrow and why do we need it for the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of a real estate transaction, is essentially a neutral third-party holding place for funds and documents. Think of it like a secure, temporary holding area for your money and the deed until all the conditions of the sale are met. It's crucial because it protects both you, the buyer, and the seller, ensuring that the money isn't handed over until the house officially changes hands, and vice versa. This process keeps the entire transaction from becoming a chaotic, unpredictable scramble, which is exactly what you want when dealing with a large purchase like a home in Toronto.",
