    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. so like who actually holds onto the money? is it just some random bank or is there a specific person in charge of guarding it all during the wait?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The entity holding the money is usually a licensed real estate professional, a title company, or a specific escrow agent, depending on the local customs in Toronto. They are the designated, trusted third party—not just any random bank teller, though banks are often involved in the process. These professionals are legally bound to manage those funds with extreme care, ensuring they are only disbursed when every single condition of the purchase agreement is satisfied. They act as the gatekeeper, making sure the deal doesn't fall apart over a misplaced dollar.",
